  <Comment id='AnomDescription'>
  These calculations are performed using scaled and merged data.  More accurate estimates of the limit of the anomalous signal
  can be obtained using scaled and unmerged data in the half dataset correlation calculation of aimless. 

 The measurability is defined as the fraction of the anomalous differences for which the signal to noise for deltaI,
  I(+) and I(-) are all > 3. The resolution limits are derived from I/sigI of 1.2 for the signal to noise, and measurability above 5% For well processed data having more than 5% of the measured data satisfying this criteria is a good
   indicator, particularly when combined with a significate mean signal to noise of the anomalous difference in a
  resolution shell.
