<Comment id="LTestDesc">
The Cumulative |L| plot for acentric data, where L = (I1-I2)/(I1+I2). This depends on the local difference in intensities.  The difference operators used link to the neighbouring reflections taking into account possible tNCS operators.  Note that this estimate is not as reliable as obtained via the H-test or ML Britton test if twin laws are available.  However, it is less prone to the effects of anisotropy than the H-test.
</Comment>
